The '''Red Flame''' was the ideal state of perfection among the [[Chiss/Legends|Chiss]]. It represented the essence of courage, cunning, and discipline. Chiss serving in the [[Chiss Expansionary Defense Force|military]], such as [[First Lieutenant/Legends|First Lieutenant]] [[Shawnkyr Nuruodo]], wore [[Red Flame (symbol)|red piping]] on their [[Flight suit/Legends|flight suits]] to remind themselves that the ideals of the Red Flame should be aspired to, though not necessarily destined to be achieved.<ref name="RSBF">{{GamerCite|7|Red Sky, Blue Flame}}</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
{{Quote|But more than that, you embody the Red Flame&mdash;our courage, our cunning and our discipline. You are a remarkable woman.|Aristocra Saganu|<ref name="Assault on the Starbreeze">{{TORcite|type=class|Imperial Agent|Assault on the Starbreeze|Hoth}}</ref>}}
Red Flame was first mentioned in the [[2001]] short story ''[[Red Sky, Blue Flame]]'', which was written by [[Elaine Cunningham]] and published within the [[Star Wars Gamer 7|seventh]] issue of the ''[[Star Wars Gamer]]'' magazine.<ref name="RSBF" /> During the mission "Assault on the Starbreeze" in the video game ''[[Star Wars: The Old Republic]]'', when playing as a [[Gender/Legends|female]] [[Chiss/Legends|Chiss]] [[Imperial Agent]] on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Hoth/Legends|Hoth]], it is possible to flirt with the Chiss [[Aristocra/Legends|Aristocra]] [[Saganu]], in which case the latter will state that the player character embodies the Red Flame.<ref name="Assault on the Starbreeze" />

